thy many a pang with thee ; Thy fears , that die of dreaded ill
An endless world of fancied woes
that mourn A love bestowed without return
blooms the rose that cannot wound
thorn that sheds the dewy tear , Or plant of feeling
sheds a charm , And locks the mind from dread of harm :
No sudden gust of wintery woes , No blast that rends the bosom's flower , No cloud that streams in endless shower
bends the eyelids to their close
she'll pour The drop of many a precious shower
In thy soft voice the softest sound , As if sweet Harmony drew near And poured her soul into my ear
— 'Twas streams of silver , rocks of gold — And walks of happiness were seen Among vocal bowers , and valleys green
tinged with many a shade of woe
Is tinged with many a shade of woe
Thou both canst give and heal the wound
Thou both canst give and heal the wound
